Record Simulation Output
Recording allows you to capture simulation output in a persistent repository. The recorded data are grouped by simulation and can then be visually inspected and compared.
  1. Configure model to log data
    Recording simulation output requires logging be correctly configured
    • Open Configuration Parameters to "Data Import/export" pane
    • Help on configuring data logging
  2. Select signals to log
    Specific signals must be selected for logging. Right-click on a signal and choose "Properties" dialog.
    • Help on logging signals
  3. Simulate model
    Simulation output will be recorded in Simulation Data Inspector, which will open automatically when the simulation is paused/stopped.
